Control Flow
	a program's control flow is the order
	in which the program's instructions or code
	statements are executed
	
	if -> condition
	
Operators:
	< - less than
	> - greater than 
	== - equal to 
	<= - less than or equal
	>= - greater than or equal
	!= = not equal to 
	
scope of variable is within the curly braces only

Loops:
	similar to if condition but runs as many times we want.
	
while loop
	while loop
	condition checking
	if true 
	goes inside 
	else
	loop comes out